<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>hang on • hang one on</xh5><p> <i>hang on</i>—(coll.) 1. continue smth. persistently; persevere with smth.: I really want to go to sleep, but I am going to <u>hang on</u> for a couple more hours. 2. keep listening on the telephone; not hang up: Please <u>hang on</u> for a minute while I find out what team you are on. I will let you know in a minute...</p><p> <i>hang one on</i>—(U.S. sl.) get very drunk: A simple statement to the barkeep—“I really <u>hung one on</u> last night”—was enough to get a little sympathy and a double Bloody Mary.</p> </entry>
